The paper deals with cyber-security and attribution of cyber-attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of classification techniques and heuristics to identify the culprit suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the limitations of previous studies, indicating a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and the use of DEFCON capture-the-flag (CTF) exercise data, which is a popular event in the cyber-security community, suggesting a focus on cyber-security (cs.CYBER).
